---
description: Session end — produce structured summary when user signals end of session
globs: []
---

Trigger when the user says any of the following (case-insensitive, partial match acceptable):

> "wrap up", "done for today", "session end", "handoff",
> "I'm done", "that's it for today", "goodbye", "EOD",
> "end of day", "logging off", "I'll stop here"

### Workflow

Read `.claude/agents/end-of-session-agent.md` and follow its full phase pipeline.

The agent handles all session-closing workflows in one deterministic sequence:
brief check → mid-session check → environment detection → state assessment → build gate → techdebt scan → git operations → todo archive → doc refresh → plan cleanup → session evaluation → write session-handoff.md → present to user → sync check.

> **Note:** The agent subsumes the previous standalone sweep + handoff workflow. Do not run `session-handoff/SKILL.md` or `sweep-stale-todos.md` separately — the agent invokes them internally.
